What you need to know:

In the program by the non-governmental organisation, whose mission is to professionalise sports in East Africa, the footballers will undergo trials under the watch of a Uefa licensed coachThe trials will be held in 11 Nairobi’s estates, namely; Mathare, Huruma, Kariobangi, Korogocho, Dandora, Kiambu, Kayole, Mukuru, Kibera, Kawangware and KangemiThe non-governmental organisation started the initiative with a men’s basketball trial between September and October last year, with more than 200 players between the age of 15 and 17 showing up, to try their luck